@startuml
title Calculator.divide() Operation Flow

start

:Call divide(a, b);

:Invoke Python / operator (a / b);

note right
  Python's / operator performs
  the zero-check natively
end note

if (b == 0?) then (yes)
  :Python raises ZeroDivisionError;
  :Exception propagates to caller;
  stop
  note right: ZeroDivisionError thrown
else (no)
  :Operator executes normal division;
  :Return result (numeric);
  stop
  note right: Return result to caller
endif

@enduml
